Third-Party Software Notices
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This project is inspired by and partially derived from the design of:

  qmd — Personal Knowledge Base Search
  Copyright (c) 2024 Tobi Lutke
  https://github.com/tobi/qmd
  License: MIT

  The overall architecture (SQLite-backed store, chunk-based FTS5 indexing,
  MCP integration, and CLI design) was informed by qmd's approach.
  seekx extends this foundation with:
    - Remote model APIs for embedding, reranking, and query expansion
    - Chinese-language FTS5 support via Jieba tokenization
    - Real-time file-system watching (chokidar)
    - PDF and plain-text document support
    - Multi-collection management
